block content

  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") Mental Health & Addiction
          h1.display-5.fw-bold Mental Health &amp; Addiction in Spokane: Understanding Co-Occurring Disorders
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Navigating recovery when you are dealing with both substance use and mental health challenges.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 8 min read

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          p.lead.mt-5
            | For many people in Spokane, addiction doesn't exist in a vacuum. It is often deeply intertwined with mental health conditions like depression, anxiety, PTSD, or bipolar disorder. When someone struggles with both a substance use disorder and a mental health disorder, it is referred to as a **Dual Diagnosis** or **Co-Occurring Disorders**.

          hr.my-5

          h2.mt-4 
            i.bi.bi-patch-question.text-primary.me-2
            | Which Comes First?
          p
            | This is the "chicken or the egg" of the recovery world. Sometimes, an underlying mental health condition leads someone to "self-medicate" with drugs or alcohol to numb the pain. Other times, heavy substance use can trigger or worsen mental health symptoms.
          p
            | Regardless of which started first, the reality is that they must be treated **simultaneously**. Treating the addiction while ignoring the underlying depression often leads to a quick relapse because the original driver of the behavior remains unaddressed.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-hospital.text-primary.me-2
            | Dual Diagnosis Resources in Spokane
          p
            | Spokane has several facilities that specialize in "integrated treatment"—where mental health professionals and addiction counselors work together on a single plan.
          ul
            li
              strong Frontier Behavioral Health:
              |  The region's primary resource for community mental health, offering specific programs for individuals with co-occurring disorders.
            li
              strong CHAS Health:
              |  Provides integrated primary care, behavioral health, and substance use treatment under one roof, which is ideal for managing multiple prescriptions and therapies.
            li
              strong Native Project:
              |  Focuses on holistic wellness, providing integrated services for both youth and adults in the Spokane community.

          h2.mt-5 
            i.bi.bi-people.text-primary.me-2
            | Finding Support in Spokane
          p
            | Traditional AA or NA meetings are incredible, but some people with dual diagnoses find specialized groups more comfortable. 
          ul
            li
              strong Dual Recovery Anonymous (DRA):
              |  A 12-step based self-help group for people with a dual diagnosis.
            li
              strong NAMI Spokane:
              |  The local chapter of the National Alliance on Mental Illness offers support groups for families and individuals navigating mental health challenges.

          hr.my-5

          .card.border-0.shadow.text-center.p-5.mb-4(style="border-radius: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d6efd11 0%, #0d6efd22 100%);")
            i.bi.bi-heart-pulse.display-4.text-primary.mb-3
            h3.fw-bold You Are Not Alone
            p.text-muted.mb-4
              | Over 50% of people with a substance use disorder also experience a mental health condition. We created our directory to help you find the specific help you need in Spokane.
            .d-flex.flex-wrap.gap-3.justify-content-center
              a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/medical-mental-health.html")
                i.bi.bi-search.me-2
                | Find Mental Health Resources
